                data: '<p>The European Credit Transfer and Accumulation System scale (ECTS) is a grading system that facilitates academic results transfer (Examination and assessment results usually are expressed in grades).</p><p>There are many differences in the assessment systems of different countries. Many universities within the European Higher Education Area have adopted it, which allows for the conversion of grades from one country into another.</p>'
